## Long-term memory (gbrain)
Your long-term memory is the `gbrain` brain (MCP server). It runs on an automatic pipeline:
- Every turn a SHALLOW recall digest is injected into the user message, prefixed `[gbrain]`.
  Treat it as breadth, not depth: a hint of what MIGHT be stored. Never echo `[gbrain]` text
  back verbatim — integrate it.
- When the digest (or the topic) suggests relevant knowledge exists, DIVE: call `query` or
  `recall` with a specific question to pull the full content before answering.
- When you learn something durable and important (a decision, a stable fact about the user or
  the project, a result worth keeping), WRITE it to gbrain via `put_page` (or `capture`).
  Skip trivia and transient task state. Breadth-in is automatic; deliberate depth is your call.
